commit.message:
Fix pcap_open_live parameters

* Set the buffer size to 64k, i.e. big enough to hold a jumbo frame
* Set the packet buffer timeout (read timeout) to 1ms as -1 was illegal on
  some platforms. (see tracebox/tracebox#54).

Signed-off-by: Olivier Tilmans <olivier.tilmans@uclouvain.be>

commit.message:
Merge pull request #49 from jarrielcook/int64_fix

Corrected pointer types used in Int64Field::Read.
Corrected pointer types used in Int64Field::Read.
Added license on README file

IPAddress Fields: Fix initialization

The human representation of null addresses is not an empty
string, fixes #43.

Signed-off-by: Olivier Tilmans <olivier.tilmans@uclouvain.be>

Merge pull request #42 from mfontanini/layer-memleak

Fix memory leak on Layer's copy constructor.
Initialize and delete Layer::raw_data properly

Fix memory leak on Layer's copy constructor.

When copy-constructing a Layer, if the object being copied's layer size
is 0, raw_layer is intialized by using a 0 size allocation. However,
Layer::~Layer only deletes raw_layer if the size > 0. In this case,
the size is 0, so it won't ever be deleted.
Allow to create malformed DHCP options

Layers: Enforced PROTO to be an enum

Signed-off-by: Olivier Tilmans <olivier.tilmans@uclouvain.be>
